      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i was looking at some satellite maps of dc and the way the roads and monuments are laid out... it's weird. if you trace the main axes from everywhere, it doesn't just look like urban planning. it looks like it was designed to follow a specific geometric pattern, almost like a symbol or a sigil. have you ever seen any analysis on the actual geometry of the dc street layout? it feels too intentional to be just for traffic.",
